<class name="CassieProfileMover" inherits="RefCounted" api_type="core" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../doc/class.xsd">
	<brief_description>
		Curvenet-driven mesh deformer — the always-on coupling between [CassieCurvenetKnot] manipulators and the underlying mesh.
	</brief_description>
	<description>
		Phase 1.4a — inverse-distance fallback that unblocks Pose-mode preview. Each mesh vertex is skinned to its 6 nearest curvenet samples with normalized inverse-distance weights at bind time. At deform time, sample displacements interpolate along each curve from its two endpoint knots, and each vertex translates by the weighted sum of sample displacements. Uniform translations reproduce exactly (∑ w_i = 1). Per-knot rotations are ignored until Phase 1.4b lands the cut-cell harmonic solve.
	</description>
